.TH TWM 1 "January 2026" "twm-0.1"
.SH NAME
twm \- tiny window manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B twm
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B twm
is a minimal reparenting-free window manager for X11, inspired by tinywm and suckless philosophy.
.PP
It supports:
- Raising windows with Super+F1 (on window under cursor)
- Moving windows with Super+Left mouse drag
- Resizing windows with Super+Right mouse drag
- Closing focused window with Super+C (sends WM_DELETE_WINDOW)
- Spawning st terminal with Super+Return
- Quitting the WM with Super+Q
.PP
Configuration is done at compile-time via
.B config.h
(edit and recompile).
.SH KEYBINDINGS
All use Mod4Mask (Super key) by default:
.TP
Super+F1
Raise window under cursor
.TP
Super+Left drag
Move window
.TP
Super+Right drag
Resize window
.TP
Super+C
Close focused window
.TP
Super+Return
Spawn st terminal
.TP
Super+Q
Quit twm
.SH CUSTOMIZATION
Copy
.B config.h
from a default if provided, modify keybindings/commands, then recompile.
.SH BUILDING
Use the provided nob.c build system:
.IP \(bu 2
./c -ci  (-c to compile, -i install), Configure nob.h in case you need specific PATH
